min Ï†s RSËœ + min Î³,Î¸,Ï†c RDIR.

(11)

where Î³, Î¸ and (Ï†c, Ï†s) are the parameters of the generator, encoder and two classiï¬ers. While in

the inference phase, we yield cËœ and yË†cËœ as the causal rationale and the causal prediction of a testing graph g, which exclude the inï¬‚uence of the non-causal part sËœ.

3 EXPERIMENTS

In this section, we conduct extensive experiments to answer the research questions:
â€¢ RQ1: How effective is DIR in discovering causal features and improving model generalization? â€¢ RQ2: What are the learning patterns and insights of DIR training? Especially, how does invariant
rationalization help to improve generalization?

3.1 SETTINGS

Datasets. We use one synthetic dataset and three real datasets of graph classiï¬cation tasks. Different GNNs are used in different datasets to achieve DIR and early stopping is exploited during training. Here we brieï¬‚y introduce the datasets, while the details of dataset statistics, deployed GNNs, and training process are summarized in Appendix D.

â€¢ Spurious-Motif is a synthetic dataset created by following Ying et al. (2019), which involves

18, 000 graphs. Each graph is composed of one base (Tree, Ladder, Wheel denoted by S = 0, 1, 2

respectively) and one motif (Cycle, House, Crane denoted by C = 0, 1, 2, respectively). The

ground-truth label Y is determined by C solely. Moreover, we manually construct false relations

of different degrees between S and label Y in the training set. Speciï¬cally, in the training set, we

sample each motif from a uniform distribution, while the distribution of its base is determined by

P (S)

=

b Ã— I(S

=

C) +

1âˆ’b 2

Ã— I(S

=

C ).

We

manipulate

b

to

create

Spurious-Motif

datasets

of distinct biases. In the testing set, the motifs and bases are randomly attached to each other.

Besides, we include graphs with large bases to further magnify the distribution gaps.

â€¢ MNIST-75sp (Knyazev et al., 2019) converts the MNIST images into 70, 000 superpixel graphs with at most 75 nodes each graph. The nodes in the graphs are superpixels, while edges are the spatial distance between the nodes. Every graph is labeled as one of 10 classes. Random noises are added to nodesâ€™ features in the testing set.

â€¢ Graph-SST2 (Yuan et al., 2020; Socher et al., 2013) Each graph is labeled by its sentence sentiment and consists of nodes representing tokens and edges indicating node relations. Graphs are split into different sets according to their average node degree to create dataset shifts.

â€¢ Molhiv (OGBG-Molhiv) (Hu et al., 2020; 2021; Wu et al., 2017) is a molecular property prediction dataset consisting of molecule graphs, where nodes are atoms, and edges are chemical bonds. Each graph is labeled according to whether a molecule inhibits HIV replication or not.

Baselines. We thoroughly compare DIR with Empirical Risk Minimization (ERM) and two classes of baselines:

â€¢ Interpretable Baselines: Graph Attention (VelicË‡kovicÂ´ et al., 2018) and graph pooling operations including ASAP (Ranjan et al., 2020), Top-k Pool (Gao & Ji, 2019) and SAG Pool (Lee et al., 2019). We use their generated masks on graph structures as rationales. We also include GSN (Bouritsas et al., 2020), a topologically-aware message passing scheme which enriches GNNs with interpretable structural features.
â€¢ Robust/Invariant Learning Baselines: Group DRO (Sagawa et al., 2019), IRM (Arjovsky et al., 2019), V-REx (Krueger et al., 2021). This class of algorithms improves the robustness and generalization for GNNs, which helps the models better generalize in unseen groups or out-of-distribution datasets. We use random groups or partitions during the model training.

We also include an ablation model of DIR, DIR-Var, which sets Î» = 0, i.e., discards the variance term in RDIR, to show the effectiveness of the variance regularization in the DIR objective.
Metrics. We use ROC-AUC for Molhiv and ACC for the other three datasets. Moreover, for Spurious-Motif dataset, we use the precision metric to evaluate the coincidence between model rationales and the ground-truth rationales, and validate the interpretability ability quantitatively.

